<head>FASTING</head><list type="altnames">
<item>EAT NOTHING</item>
<item>ABSTAIN FROM FOOD</item>
<item>REFRAIN FROM EATING</item>
<item>GO WITHOUT FOOD</item>
<item>GO HUNGRY</item>
<item>STARVE ONESELF</item>
<item>GO ON A HUNGER STRIKE</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">持齋</item><item xml:lang="och">齊</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>AVOID EATING SOME THINGS, CONFORMING to RITUAL FORBID:prohibitions.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for the ritually purifying act of fasting is zhāi 齋.</p>
<p>2. Jiè 戒 can refer to the ritual observance of prohibitions against eating or drinking at certain times.</p></div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>SACRIFICE 17.</p>
<p>齋，齊心之意，即祭祀之前或其他重要活動前沐浴別居，清心寡欲，去除雜念，保持心境純一，以示虔誠。</p>
<p>戒，強調的是戒除不當的言行。</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>持齋</p>
<p>吃齋</p>
<p>齋戒</p>
<p>戒食</p>
<p>禁食</p>
<p>把齋</p>
<p>絕食</p>
<p>打齋</p>
